description: The otter originally surfaced almost right next to me, surprising both of us. It immediately went under, deep enough to leave no trace of where it was going. I stayed still for some time without seeing any movement, then headed down the slough in the direction I was pretty sure it had gone. Soon I saw it on the shore, was slow to get the photo but managed right before it dove back into the slough, where it visibly swam across the slough and then disappeared again.
Otter #2.

Otter #1 : First spotted in the water on the east side of the bridge.  He later crossed under the bridge and attacked a cat on the dock.  The cat yowled loudly and seems to have given the otter a couple of scratches on the left paw and just above the left eye.
